      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.Item.63q7sFrEiOS4UMQ2]{Pistol Dancer}</p>\n<p>You learn to treat a pistol as an extension of your body. Sleight of Hand becomes a class skill for you. You can @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.JournalEntry.U37n5tY5hn1ctzQL.JournalEntryPage.SKgwxeMd2gB1g2W8#reload]{Reload} a small arm as a swift action, and you can wield a small arm in melee combat as if it were a battleglove with an item level equal to or lower than your soldier level.</p>\n<p>(Level 1) @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.equipment.Item.c5r8NO1jCHPWRCx8]{Battleglove, cestus}</p>\n<p>(Level 10) @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.equipment.Item.E87mmoMwyYjdQGPK]{Battleglove, power}</p>\n<p>(Level 13) @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.equipment.Item.UzAt6lBy2YwbmZ9F]{Battleglove, nova}</p>\n<p>(Level 17) @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.equipment.Item.SZXXDCqMI6GMpFld]{Battleglove, gravity}</p>\n<p><em>(You will need to manually edit the details of the Soldier class feature to add Sleight of Hand as a Class skill)</em></p>"
